data.text:
Personal

Coached by Leandro Afini

Currently resides in Rio de Janeiro

Favorite surface is clay and favorite tournament is Wimbledon

Began playing tennis aged seven and favorite players were Roger Federer and Max Mirnyi

Sponsored by Head and Lotto

Career Highlights

DOUBLES

Winner (1): 2023 - Bogota (w/Khromacheva)

WTA 125 Titles - Doubles (1): 2024 - Contrexeville (w/Kalashnikova),Puerto Vallarta (w/Zarazua)

Career in Review

Won doubles title at 2023 Bogota (w/Khromacheva, d. Kalashnikova/Piter in F)

Ended the 2022 season by winning 21 of last 26 matches, claiming two ITF Circuit titles, including at W60 event in Rio de Janeiro

Fell 1r on WTA debut at 2022 Cleveland (as LL, l. eventual champion Samsonova)

Owns 13 titles in singles and 13 in doubles on ITF Circuit

As a junior, reached QF at Roland Garros and US Open, while was R-Up at 2013 Wimbledon (w/Kalinina, l. Krejcikova/Siniakova)
